sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant User as User<br/>(kubectl/Dashboard)
    participant APIServer as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant ODHWebhook as odh-notebook-controller<br/>Webhook 8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant ODHCtrl as odh-notebook-controller<br/>Reconciler
    participant NBCtrl as notebook-controller<br/>Reconciler
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as Jupyter Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant CullCtrl as Culling Controller

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: Notebook Creation (Auth Mode)
        User->>APIServer: POST Notebook CR<br/>Auth: User credentials
        APIServer->>ODHWebhook: Mutating Webhook<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS (serving cert)
        Note over ODHWebhook: Injects kube-rbac-proxy sidecar,<br/>resolves ImageStream tags,<br/>mounts CA bundles,<br/>sets Elyra/MLflow/Feast config
        ODHWebhook-->>APIServer: Mutated Notebook CR
        APIServer->>ODHCtrl: Watch event (Notebook created)
        ODHCtrl->>APIServer: Create HTTPRoute<br/>(nb-{ns}-{name})
        ODHCtrl->>APIServer: Create ReferenceGrant<br/>(cross-namespace)
        ODHCtrl->>APIServer: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>(controller-access + krbp-access)
        ODHCtrl->>APIServer: Create Service, SA,<br/>ClusterRoleBinding for kube-rbac-proxy
        APIServer->>NBCtrl: Watch event (Notebook created)
        NBCtrl->>APIServer: Create StatefulSet<br/>(replicas=1)
        NBCtrl->>APIServer: Create Service<br/>({notebook-name} 80→8888)
        Note over NBCtrl: Pod starts with Jupyter +<br/>kube-rbac-proxy containers
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 2: Notebook Access via Gateway (Auth Mode)
        User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
        Gateway->>KRBP: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS (serving cert)<br/>Bearer token forwarded
        KRBP->>APIServer: TokenReview<br/>HTTPS/6443
        APIServer-->>KRBP: Token valid, user identity
        KRBP->>APIServer: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(GET kubeflow.org/v1.notebooks)
        APIServer-->>KRBP: Access granted
        KRBP->>Jupyter: Proxy request<br/>HTTP/8888 (localhost)<br/>Headers: X-Auth-Request-User,<br/>X-Auth-Request-Groups
        Jupyter-->>KRBP: Response
        KRBP-->>Gateway: Response
        Gateway-->>User: HTTPS Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        Note over CullCtrl,Jupyter: Flow 3: Idle Notebook Culling
        loop Every IDLENESS_CHECK_PERIOD minutes
            CullCtrl->>Jupyter: GET /api/kernels<br/>HTTP/8888, No Auth
            Jupyter-->>CullCtrl: Kernel list (last_activity)
            CullCtrl->>Jupyter: GET /api/terminals<br/>HTTP/8888, No Auth
            Jupyter-->>CullCtrl: Terminal list (last_activity)
            alt Idle > CULL_IDLE_TIME (default 24h)
                CullCtrl->>APIServer: Patch Notebook:<br/>kubeflow-resource-stopped annotation
                APIServer->>NBCtrl: Watch event (annotation changed)
                NBCtrl->>APIServer: Scale StatefulSet replicas=0
            end
        end
    end
